# Cheatsheet collapse chords (2026-06-21 — moved off lowercase z/Z so
# vim's `z` fold-prefix + `ZZ` save-quit don't collide):
#   - `C` toggles the focused section's collapsed state.
#   - `X` toggles collapse-all ↔ expand-all.
#
# `X` collapses everything UNLESS all sections are already collapsed
# (then it expands all). So collapsing ONE section with `C` and then
# pressing `X` collapses the REST — it must NOT wipe the single
# collapse (the old `Z` asymmetry bug, now fixed).

write hello.rs "fn main() {}"
open hello.rs

command view.cheatsheet
expect screen contains "Cheatsheet"

# Step 1: collapse the focused section with `C`.
key C
expect screen contains "(collapsed)"

# Step 2: `X` with one section collapsed → collapse_all (not expand_all),
# so sections stay collapsed rather than the single collapse being wiped.
key X
expect screen contains "(collapsed)"
